Gauteng Premier David Makhura has backtracked on making Panyaza Lesufi the MEC for finance and e-Government. Makhura announced on Friday morning that Panyaza will return to his previous post as the Education and Youth Development MEC. He said the new MEC of Finance and e-Government will be Nomantu Nkomo-Ralehoko. “I have now decided that MEC Panyaza Lesufi will return to the Education portfolio as the MEC for Education & Youth Development. “I have further decided that MEC Nomantu Nkomo-Ralehoko will be the MEC for Finance & e-Government. Let the team get to work & serve the people of GP,” Makhura tweeted on Friday. 